 to ISd, it seems to be applied to a body other than that of a human being tropically: (TA:) the [golden] calf of the Children of Israel cried, but did not eat nor drink; [wherefore it is termed"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 424}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jsd", "text_ar": "جسد"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ";] and in the Kur [vii. 146 and xx. 90],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jasadFA", "text_ar": "جَسَدًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a substitute for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EijolFA", "text_ar": "عِجْلًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", or it may be meant for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*aA jasadK", "text_ar": "ذَا جَسَدٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (L:) [but see another explanation of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jsdA", "text_ar": "جسدا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as there used, below:] or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jasadN", "text_ar": "جَسَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badanN", "text_ar": "بَدَنٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[which is generally held to signify the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "body without the head and arms and legs"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (S, A:) the pl. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^ajosaAdN", "text_ar": "اَجْسَادٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Lh, Msb, TA.) Lh mentions the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_in~ahaA laHasanapu AlA^ajosaAdi", "text_ar": "اـِنَّهَا لَحَسَنَةُ الاَجْسَادِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Verily she is beautiful in respect of body"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; as though the sing. of which the pl. is thus used were applied to every separate part. (TA.)       -A2-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Saffron;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb, K) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jisaAdN", "text_ar": "جِسَادٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Lth, IAar, ISk, S, A, Msb, K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a similar dye:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S:) and ↓ the latter signifies also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a similar dye;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lth, Msb,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "red,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "intensely yellow:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lth, TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bastard saffron;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EuSofurN", "text_ar": "عُصْفُرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Msb;) and so the former word. (L.) ―         -b2-  Also, (S, L, Msb, K,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jasidN", "text_ar": "جَسِدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L, K) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jaAsidN", "text_ar": "جَاسِدٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L, Msb, K) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jasiydN", "text_ar": "جَسِيدٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L, K) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jisaAdN", "text_ar": "جِسَادٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (R,) (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Blood;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S;) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mujosadN", "text_ar": "مُجْسَدٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as being likened to saffron: (Ham p. 215:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "dry blood:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(R, L, Msb, K:) pl. of the first as above. (Ham p. 127.) ―         -b3-  Some say that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EijolFA jasadFA", "text_ar": "عِجْلًا جَسَدًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the Kur, [in two verses referred to above,] means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A red golden calf."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S.)"}], "source_refs": ["L", "TA", "S", "A", "Msb", "K", "Lth", "IAar", "ISk", "R"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-14", "pipeline_vers